title.rendered: Boosting Women led enterprises to Enterprise Europe Network-European Innovation Council networks-Workshop

content.rendered:
Prishtina REA is selected as a CIL and LN under the project 𝐄𝐄𝐍𝟐𝐄𝐈𝐂, funded by European Commission for supporting 𝑺𝒆𝒂𝒍 𝒐𝒇 𝑬𝒙𝒄𝒆𝒍𝒍𝒆𝒏𝒄𝒆 holders. EEN2EIC a European Union funded project aims to enhance collaboration and innovation by connecting businesses, particularly SMEs, with the European Innovation Council. The project facilitates opportunities for businesses to access funding, support, and networking to promote innovation and growth in the European business landscape.

 

The project facilitates opportunities for businesses to access funding, support, and networking to promote innovation and growth in the European business landscape.
The EEN2EIC (Enterprise Europe Network to European Innovation Council) project aims to extend the breadth of supporting activities EEN can provide to women entrepreneurs, widening countries and Seal of Excellence (SoE) holders.

 

The goal is to create a bridge between the two projects in order to support innovation, scale up companies and involve the most relevant actors in the EIC and EEN landscape
One of our key activities will be supporting the innovative business and women led businesses ghat aims to apply and or explore partnership opportunities towards EEN and EIC

Thus, we are organizing an information Workshop with targets on 23 of October, from 15:00 to 17:30 at Europe House, discussing about criteria's, procedures, business segments supported by EIC.
